  "body": "(Reopened from the issue #25507)\r\n\r\nThanks for the response to the previous issue that I reported.\r\nI agree that an uncle is not a block object, but what I pointed out was the \"return value\" of uncle-returning APIs.\r\n\r\nFor example, the Ethereum API specification requires `transactions` field in the returned objects of `eth_getUncleByBlockHashAndIndex` API.\r\n(Reference: https://ethereum.org/ko/developers/docs/apis/json-rpc/#eth_getunclebyblockhashandindex)\r\n\r\nI guess you included `uncles` field in the returned objects for the same reason although an omners list is not part of block header either. Also, all other client implementations include `transactions: []` entry in their returned objects.\r\n\r\nI would appreciate it if you consider this issue again based on my explanations here.\r\nThanks.\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\nGeth version: 1.10.21-stable\r\nOS & Version: Ubuntu 20.04.4 LTS\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nWhen `eth_getUncleByBlockHashAndIndex` is called, Geth should return an object of the following form:\r\n<pre>\r\n{\r\n  ...\r\n  timestamp: 1659702502,\r\n  transactions: [],\r\n  transactionsRoot: '0x40d6b6bd0d7dfd3b17e88badf51a075ff5196271d10a892acacfefeef549cf5a',\r\n  uncles: []\r\n}\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nGeth returns an object without `transactions` field:\r\n<pre>\r\n{\r\n  ...\r\n  timestamp: 1659702502,\r\n  transactionsRoot: '0x40d6b6bd0d7dfd3b17e88badf51a075ff5196271d10a892acacfefeef549cf5a',\r\n  uncles: []\r\n}\r\n</pre>",
